headline: PRU Q2 Deep Dive: Product Diversification and Cost Initiatives Offset Margin Pressures
summary: Financial services giant Prudential Financial (NYSE:PRU) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales falling 2.5% year on year to $13.51 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $3.58 per share was 11.1% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: 5 Revealing Analyst Questions From Prudential’s Q2 Earnings Call
summary: Prudential's second quarter results elicited a positive market reaction, despite revenue falling short of Wall Street expectations. Management emphasized that improved underwriting and higher investment spread income across global insurance businesses were central to performance, while the group insurance segment delivered one of its best quarters in recent memory.
